6450/**
6451 * ata_host_register - register initialized ATA host
6452 * @host: ATA host to register
6453 * @sht: template for SCSI host
6454 *
6455 * Register initialized ATA host. @host is allocated using
6456 * ata_host_alloc() and fully initialized by LLD. This function
6457 * starts ports, registers @host with ATA and SCSI layers and
6458 * probe registered devices.
6459 *
6460 * LOCKING:
6461 * Inherited from calling layer (may sleep).
6462 *
6463 * RETURNS:
6464 * 0 on success, -errno otherwise.
6465 */
6466int ata_host_register(struct ata_host *host, struct scsi_host_template *sht)
6467{
6468 int i, rc;
6469
6470 host->n_tags = clamp(sht->can_queue, 1, ATA_MAX_QUEUE - 1);
6471
6472 /* host must have been started */
6473 if (!(host->flags & ATA_HOST_STARTED)) {
6474 dev_err(host->dev, "BUG: trying to register unstarted host\n");
6475 WARN_ON(1);
6476 return -EINVAL;
6477 }
6478
6479 /* Blow away unused ports. This happens when LLD can't
6480 * determine the exact number of ports to allocate at
6481 * allocation time.
6482 */
6483 for (i = host->n_ports; host->ports[i]; i++)
6484 kfree(host->ports[i]);
6485
6486 /* give ports names and add SCSI hosts */
6487 for (i = 0; i < host->n_ports; i++) {
6488 host->ports[i]->print_id = atomic_inc_return(&ata_print_id);
6489 host->ports[i]->local_port_no = i + 1;
6490 }
6491
6492 /* Create associated sysfs transport objects */
6493 for (i = 0; i < host->n_ports; i++) {
6494 rc = ata_tport_add(host->dev,host->ports[i]);
6495 if (rc) {
6496 goto err_tadd;
6497 }
6498 }
6499
6500 rc = ata_scsi_add_hosts(host, sht);
6501 if (rc)
6502 goto err_tadd;
6503
6504 /* set cable, sata_spd_limit and report */
6505 for (i = 0; i < host->n_ports; i++) {
6506 struct ata_port *ap = host->ports[i];
6507 unsigned long xfer_mask;
6508
6509 /* set SATA cable type if still unset */
6510 if (ap->cbl == ATA_CBL_NONE && (ap->flags & ATA_FLAG_SATA))
6511 ap->cbl = ATA_CBL_SATA;
6512
6513 /* init sata_spd_limit to the current value */
6514 sata_link_init_spd(&ap->link);
6515 if (ap->slave_link)
6516 sata_link_init_spd(ap->slave_link);
6517
6518 /* print per-port info to dmesg */
6519 xfer_mask = ata_pack_xfermask(ap->pio_mask, ap->mwdma_mask,
6520 ap->udma_mask);
6521
6522 if (!ata_port_is_dummy(ap)) {
6523 ata_port_info(ap, "%cATA max %s %s\n",
6524 (ap->flags & ATA_FLAG_SATA) ? 'S' : 'P',
6525 ata_mode_string(xfer_mask),
6526 ap->link.eh_info.desc);
6527 ata_ehi_clear_desc(&ap->link.eh_info);
6528 } else
6529 ata_port_info(ap, "DUMMY\n");
6530 }
6531
6532 /* perform each probe asynchronously */
6533 for (i = 0; i < host->n_ports; i++) {
6534 struct ata_port *ap = host->ports[i];
6535 async_schedule(async_port_probe, ap);
6536 }
6537
6538 return 0;
6539
6540 err_tadd:
6541 while (--i >= 0) {
6542 ata_tport_delete(host->ports[i]);
6543 }
6544 return rc;
6545
6546}
6547
6548/**
6549 * ata_host_activate - start host, request IRQ and register it
6550 * @host: target ATA host
6551 * @irq: IRQ to request
6552 * @irq_handler: irq_handler used when requesting IRQ
6553 * @irq_flags: irq_flags used when requesting IRQ
6554 * @sht: scsi_host_template to use when registering the host
6555 *
6556 * After allocating an ATA host and initializing it, most libata
6557 * LLDs perform three steps to activate the host - start host,
6558 * request IRQ and register it. This helper takes necessary
6559 * arguments and performs the three steps in one go.
6560 *
6561 * An invalid IRQ skips the IRQ registration and expects the host to
6562 * have set polling mode on the port. In this case, @irq_handler
6563 * should be NULL.
6564 *
6565 * LOCKING:
6566 * Inherited from calling layer (may sleep).
6567 *
6568 * RETURNS:
6569 * 0 on success, -errno otherwise.
6570 */
6571int ata_host_activate(struct ata_host *host, int irq,
6572 irq_handler_t irq_handler, unsigned long irq_flags,
6573 struct scsi_host_template *sht)
6574{
6575 int i, rc;
6576 char *irq_desc;
6577
6578 rc = ata_host_start(host);
6579 if (rc)
6580 return rc;
6581
6582 /* Special case for polling mode */
6583 if (!irq) {
6584 WARN_ON(irq_handler);
6585 return ata_host_register(host, sht);
6586 }
6587
6588 irq_desc = devm_kasprintf(host->dev, GFP_KERNEL, "%s[%s]",
6589 dev_driver_string(host->dev),
6590 dev_name(host->dev));
6591 if (!irq_desc)
6592 return -ENOMEM;
6593
6594 rc = devm_request_irq(host->dev, irq, irq_handler, irq_flags,
6595 irq_desc, host);
6596 if (rc)
6597 return rc;
6598
6599 for (i = 0; i < host->n_ports; i++)
6600 ata_port_desc(host->ports[i], "irq %d", irq);
6601
6602 rc = ata_host_register(host, sht);
6603 /* if failed, just free the IRQ and leave ports alone */
6604 if (rc)
6605 devm_free_irq(host->dev, irq, host);
6606
6607 return rc;
6608}

6610/**
6611 * ata_port_detach - Detach ATA port in preparation of device removal
6612 * @ap: ATA port to be detached
6613 *
6614 * Detach all ATA devices and the associated SCSI devices of @ap;
6615 * then, remove the associated SCSI host. @ap is guaranteed to
6616 * be quiescent on return from this function.
6617 *
6618 * LOCKING:
6619 * Kernel thread context (may sleep).
6620 */
6621static void ata_port_detach(struct ata_port *ap)
6622{
6623 unsigned long flags;
6624 struct ata_link *link;
6625 struct ata_device *dev;
6626
6627 if (!ap->ops->error_handler)
6628 goto skip_eh;
6629
6630 /* tell EH we're leaving & flush EH */
6631 spin_lock_irqsave(ap->lock, flags);
6632 ap->pflags |= ATA_PFLAG_UNLOADING;
6633 ata_port_schedule_eh(ap);
6634 spin_unlock_irqrestore(ap->lock, flags);
6635
6636 /* wait till EH commits suicide */
6637 ata_port_wait_eh(ap);
6638
6639 /* it better be dead now */
6640 WARN_ON(!(ap->pflags & ATA_PFLAG_UNLOADED));
6641
6642 cancel_delayed_work_sync(&ap->hotplug_task);
6643
6644 skip_eh:
6645 /* clean up zpodd on port removal */
6646 ata_for_each_link(link, ap, HOST_FIRST) {
6647 ata_for_each_dev(dev, link, ALL) {
6648 if (zpodd_dev_enabled(dev))
6649 zpodd_exit(dev);
6650 }
6651 }
6652 if (ap->pmp_link) {
6653 int i;
6654 for (i = 0; i < SATA_PMP_MAX_PORTS; i++)
6655 ata_tlink_delete(&ap->pmp_link[i]);
6656 }
6657 /* remove the associated SCSI host */
6658 scsi_remove_host(ap->scsi_host);
6659 ata_tport_delete(ap);
6660}
6661
6662/**
6663 * ata_host_detach - Detach all ports of an ATA host
6664 * @host: Host to detach
6665 *
6666 * Detach all ports of @host.
6667 *
6668 * LOCKING:
6669 * Kernel thread context (may sleep).
6670 */
6671void ata_host_detach(struct ata_host *host)
6672{
6673 int i;
6674
6675 for (i = 0; i < host->n_ports; i++)
6676 ata_port_detach(host->ports[i]);
6677
6678 /* the host is dead now, dissociate ACPI */
6679 ata_acpi_dissociate(host);
6680}

6702/* move to PCI subsystem */
6703int pci_test_config_bits(struct pci_dev *pdev, const struct pci_bits *bits)
6704{
6705 unsigned long tmp = 0;
6706
6707 switch (bits->width) {
6708 case 1: {
6709 u8 tmp8 = 0;
6710 pci_read_config_byte(pdev, bits->reg, &tmp8);
6711 tmp = tmp8;
6712 break;
6713 }
6714 case 2: {
6715 u16 tmp16 = 0;
6716 pci_read_config_word(pdev, bits->reg, &tmp16);
6717 tmp = tmp16;
6718 break;
6719 }
6720 case 4: {
6721 u32 tmp32 = 0;
6722 pci_read_config_dword(pdev, bits->reg, &tmp32);
6723 tmp = tmp32;
6724 break;
6725 }
6726
6727 default:
6728 return -EINVAL;
6729 }
6730
6731 tmp &= bits->mask;
6732
6733 return (tmp == bits->val) ? 1 : 0;
6734}

6874 int nr_matches = 0, i;
6875
6876 /* find where this param ends and update *cur */
6877 while (*p != '\0' && *p != ',')
6878 p++;
6879
6880 if (*p == '\0')
6881 *cur = p;
6882 else
6883 *cur = p + 1;

6885 *p = '\0';
6886
6887 /* parse */
6888 p = strchr(start, ':');
6889 if (!p) {
6890 val = strstrip(start);
6891 goto parse_val;
6892 }
6893 *p = '\0';
6894
6895 id = strstrip(start);
6896 val = strstrip(p + 1);
6897
6898 /* parse id */
6899 p = strchr(id, '.');
6900 if (p) {
6901 *p++ = '\0';
6902 force_ent->device = simple_strtoul(p, &endp, 10);
6903 if (p == endp || *endp != '\0') {
6904 *reason = "invalid device";
6905 return -EINVAL;
6906 }
6907 }
6908
6909 force_ent->port = simple_strtoul(id, &endp, 10);
6910 if (id == endp || *endp != '\0') {
6911 *reason = "invalid port/link";
6912 return -EINVAL;
6913 }
6914
6915 parse_val:
6916 /* parse val, allow shortcuts so that both 1.5 and 1.5Gbps work */
6917 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(force_tbl); i++) {
6918 const struct ata_force_param *fp = &force_tbl[i];
6919
6920 if (strncasecmp(val, fp->name, strlen(val)))
6921 continue;
6922
6923 nr_matches++;
6924 match_fp = fp;
6925
6926 if (strcasecmp(val, fp->name) == 0) {
6927 nr_matches = 1;
6928 break;
6929 }
6930 }
6931
6932 if (!nr_matches) {
6933 *reason = "unknown value";
6934 return -EINVAL;
6935 }
6936 if (nr_matches > 1) {
6937 *reason = "ambigious value";
6938 return -EINVAL;
6939 }
6940
6941 force_ent->param = *match_fp;
6942
6943 return 0;
6944}
6945
6946static void __init ata_parse_force_param(void)
6947{
6948 int idx = 0, size = 1;
6949 int last_port = -1, last_device = -1;
6950 char *p, *cur, *next;
6951
6952 /* calculate maximum number of params and allocate force_tbl */
6953 for (p = ata_force_param_buf; *p; p++)
6954 if (*p == ',')
6955 size++;
6956
6957 ata_force_tbl = kzalloc(sizeof(ata_force_tbl[0]) * size, GFP_KERNEL);
6958 if (!ata_force_tbl) {
6959 printk(KERN_WARNING "ata: failed to extend force table, "
6960 "libata.force ignored\n");
6961 return;
6962 }
6963
6964 /* parse and populate the table */
6965 for (cur = ata_force_param_buf; *cur != '\0'; cur = next) {
6966 const char *reason = "";
6967 struct ata_force_ent te = { .port = -1, .device = -1 };
6968
6969 next = cur;
6970 if (ata_parse_force_one(&next, &te, &reason)) {
6971 printk(KERN_WARNING "ata: failed to parse force "
6972 "parameter \"%s\" (%s)\n",
6973 cur, reason);
6974 continue;
6975 }
6976
6977 if (te.port == -1) {
6978 te.port = last_port;
6979 te.device = last_device;
6980 }
6981
6982 ata_force_tbl[idx++] = te;
6983
6984 last_port = te.port;
6985 last_device = te.device;
6986 }
6987
6988 ata_force_tbl_size = idx;
6989}

6991static int __init ata_init(void)
6992{
6993 int rc;
6994
6995 ata_parse_force_param();
6996
6997 rc = ata_sff_init();
6998 if (rc) {
6999 kfree(ata_force_tbl);
7000 return rc;
7001 }
7002
7003 libata_transport_init();
7004 ata_scsi_transport_template = ata_attach_transport();
7005 if (!ata_scsi_transport_template) {
7006 ata_sff_exit();
7007 rc = -ENOMEM;
7008 goto err_out;
7009 }
7010
7011 printk(KERN_DEBUG "libata version " DRV_VERSION " loaded.\n");
7012 return 0;
7013
7014err_out:
7015 return rc;
7016}

7024}

7036/**
7037 * ata_msleep - ATA EH owner aware msleep
7038 * @ap: ATA port to attribute the sleep to
7039 * @msecs: duration to sleep in milliseconds
7040 *
7041 * Sleeps @msecs. If the current task is owner of @ap's EH, the
7042 * ownership is released before going to sleep and reacquired
7043 * after the sleep is complete. IOW, other ports sharing the
7044 * @ap->host will be allowed to own the EH while this task is
7045 * sleeping.
7046 *
7047 * LOCKING:
7048 * Might sleep.
7049 */
7050void ata_msleep(struct ata_port *ap, unsigned int msecs)
7051{
7052 bool owns_eh = ap && ap->host->eh_owner == current;
7053
7054 if (owns_eh)
7055 ata_eh_release(ap);
7056
7057 if (msecs < 20) {
7058 unsigned long usecs = msecs * USEC_PER_MSEC;
7059 usleep_range(usecs, usecs + 50);
7060 } else {
7061 msleep(msecs);
7062 }
7063
7064 if (owns_eh)
7065 ata_eh_acquire(ap);
7066}
7067
7068/**
7069 * ata_wait_register - wait until register value changes
7070 * @ap: ATA port to wait register for, can be NULL
7071 * @reg: IO-mapped register
7072 * @mask: Mask to apply to read register value
7073 * @val: Wait condition
7074 * @interval: polling interval in milliseconds
7075 * @timeout: timeout in milliseconds
7076 *
7077 * Waiting for some bits of register to change is a common
7078 * operation for ATA controllers. This function reads 32bit LE
7079 * IO-mapped register @reg and tests for the following condition.
7080 *
7081 * (*@reg & mask) != val
7082 *
7083 * If the condition is met, it returns; otherwise, the process is
7084 * repeated after @interval_msec until timeout.
7085 *
7086 * LOCKING:
7087 * Kernel thread context (may sleep)
7088 *
7089 * RETURNS:
7090 * The final register value.
7091 */
7092u32 ata_wait_register(struct ata_port *ap, void __iomem *reg, u32 mask, u32 val,
7093 unsigned long interval, unsigned long timeout)
7094{
7095 unsigned long deadline;
7096 u32 tmp;
7097
7098 tmp = ioread32(reg);
7099
7100 /* Calculate timeout _after_ the first read to make sure
7101 * preceding writes reach the controller before starting to
7102 * eat away the timeout.
7103 */
7104 deadline = ata_deadline(jiffies, timeout);
7105
7106 while ((tmp & mask) == val && time_before(jiffies, deadline)) {
7107 ata_msleep(ap, interval);
7108 tmp = ioread32(reg);
7109 }
7110
7111 return tmp;
7112}
7113
7114/**
7115 * sata_lpm_ignore_phy_events - test if PHY event should be ignored
7116 * @link: Link receiving the event
7117 *
7118 * Test whether the received PHY event has to be ignored or not.
7119 *
7120 * LOCKING:
7121 * None:
7122 *
7123 * RETURNS:
7124 * True if the event has to be ignored.
7125 */
7126bool sata_lpm_ignore_phy_events(struct ata_link *link)
7127{
7128 unsigned long lpm_timeout = link->last_lpm_change +
7129 msecs_to_jiffies(ATA_TMOUT_SPURIOUS_PHY);
7130
7131 /* if LPM is enabled, PHYRDY doesn't mean anything */
7132 if (link->lpm_policy > ATA_LPM_MAX_POWER)
7133 return true;
7134
7135 /* ignore the first PHY event after the LPM policy changed
7136 * as it is might be spurious
7137 */
7138 if ((link->flags & ATA_LFLAG_CHANGED) &&
7139 time_before(jiffies, lpm_timeout))
7140 return true;
7141
7142 return false;
7143}
7144EXPORT_SYMBOL_GPL(sata_lpm_ignore_phy_events);
